{"cursor":"3215","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Robert Hakim' (19 December 1907 – 9 February 1992) and 'Raymond Hakim'\n(23 August 1909 – 14 August 1980) were Egyptian-born brothers who usually\nworked in collaboration as film producers in France and other European\ncountries. Their brother AndrÃ© Hakim is also a film producer.\n\nInitially working for the American company Paramount, they formed the company\nParis-Film Production in 1934, Liz-Anne Bawden (ed) The Oxford Companion to\nFilm, 1976, Oxford: OUP, p316 and financed Julien Duvivier's [[PÃ©pÃ© le\nMoko]] in 1936, Jean Renoir's [[La BÃªte Humaine (film)|La BÃªte Humaine]] (1938)\nand Marcel CarnÃ©'s [[Le Jour se lÃ¨ve]] (Daybreak 1939), all starring Jean Gabin,\nbefore the brothers emigrated to the United States.\n\nAfter the war they worked on several American films, including Renoir's [[The\nSoutherner (1945 film)|The Southerner]] (1945) and [[The Long Night (1947\nfilm)|The Long Night]], a remake of Le Jour se lÃ¨ve with Henry Fonda.\n\nIn 1950 they returned to France and embarked on producing films aimed at an\ninternational audience. [[Casque d'or]] (1953) effectively launched the career\nof Simone Signoret and [[Purple Noon|Plein Soleil]] (1960) did the same for\nAlain Delon. [[The Hunchback of Notre Dame (1956 film)|Notre Dame de Paris]]\nwith Anthony Quinn as Quasimodo and Gina Lollobrigida as Esmeralda was\ninternationally successful, but not critically well received.\n\nIn the 1960s they made two films with a [[nouvelle vague]] director, Claude\nChabrol with Ã double tour (1959) and Les Bonnes Femmes (1960), but worked with\nolder directors (Luis BuÃ±uel [[Belle de Jour (film)|Belle de jour]] 1968)\nsometimes relatively new to international audiences (Michelangelo Antonioni\n[[Eclipse (1962 film)|L'eclisse]] 1962). They also worked with Roger Vadim on a\nremake of [[La Ronde (1964 film)|La Ronde]] (1964), which starred Vadim's then\nwife, Jane Fonda.\n\nThe Hakim's have a mixed reputation; American director Joseph Losey had an\nespecially fraught relationship with them while making [[Eva (1962 film)|Eva]]\n(1962). In post-production, Losey and his team found the film had been recut\nduring the weekend without their consultation; Losey and Robert Hakim almost\ncame to blows. Michel Legrand was commissioned for the score without\nconsultation too, but like actor Jeanne Moreau, was not paid any fee. David\nCaute Joseph Losey: A Revenge on Life, 1994, London: Faber, p137\n","linknr":113,"url":"Robert_and_Raymond_Hakim","recorded":1375069354,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Robert_and_Raymond_Hakim&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Robert_and_Raymond_Hakim&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Andr%C3%A9_Hakim","/wiki/Paramount_Pictures","#cite_note-1","/wiki/Julien_Duvivier","/wiki/P%C3%A9p%C3%A9_le_Moko","/wiki/Jean_Renoir","/wiki/La_B%C3%AAte_Humaine_(film)","/wiki/Marcel_Carn%C3%A9","/wiki/Le_Jour_se_l%C3%A8ve","/wiki/Jean_Gabin","/wiki/The_Southerner_(1945_film)","/wiki/The_Long_Night_(1947_film)","/wiki/Henry_Fonda","/wiki/Casque_d%27or","/wiki/Simone_Signoret","/wiki/Purple_Noon","/wiki/Alain_Delon","/wiki/The_Hunchback_of_Notre_Dame_(1956_film)","/wiki/Anthony_Quinn"